text.tspan: Share of land defined as natural habitat
Natural ecosystems include forest, grassland, savanna, and shrublands, and other classes such as
peatlands and marshes. It is total land minus land that is used by humans for agriculture – either
croplands or pasture – or for infrastructure and urban environments.
Data source: Calculated by Our World in Data based on Taylor & Rising (2021)
